                            <comment id="12612948" author="jdcryans" created="Fri, 11 Jul 2008 18:08:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Correction, REST and Thrift APIs only refer to it, nothing is enforced.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12612964" author="jdcryans" created="Fri, 11 Jul 2008 19:03:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;First try at validating values length.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12613380" author="jdcryans" created="Mon, 14 Jul 2008 17:21:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The first patch broke the build in TestTable, had to put the validation code at the HRS level. On the good side, in the first patch the getTableDescription did an RPC at each validation which was somewhat bad so having it in HRS is more direct.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Review please.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
